    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-13T14:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-13T14:45:00-05:00" n="511"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d511">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">713.1311/239: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-13T14:00:00-05:45"
                            >February 13, 1934—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 8:14 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. My 45, February 9, 4 p.m. President Sacasa showed me last night telegram from
                    President Jiménez accepting invitation on behalf of Costa Rica but suggesting
                    that date of Conference be postponed until March 15th and that summary agenda be
                    communicated to the interested Governments and (2) telegram from President Ubico
                    dated February 12, acknowledging receipt of Sacasa’s telegram (embodying above
                    mentioned message from Costa Rica) but making no change in the date.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
